block_defaults_parameter_items_per_page                                       = Standard list block parameter, which specifies the number of elements per page (if pagination is enabled for block) or total displayed elements count. Specify [kt|b]0[/kt|b] to load all available %type_names% (may overload your server memory).
block_defaults_parameter_links_per_page                                       = Standard list block parameter, which specifies the maximum number of pagination links shown at the same time (if pagination is enabled for block).
block_defaults_parameter_var_from                                             = URL parameter, which provides pagination information. Should be specified to enable pagination for this block.
block_defaults_parameter_var_items_per_page                                   = URL parameter, which provides number of elements per page. Overrides [kt|b]items_per_page[/kt|b] value if URL parameter contains positive number.
block_defaults_parameter_sort_by                                              = Standard list block parameter, which specifies list sorting.
block_defaults_parameter_var_sort_by                                          = Enables dynamic sorting by the value provided in this URL parameter. Overrides [kt|b]sort_by[/kt|b] parameter. The following values can be passed in URL: %1%.
block_defaults_parameter_var_context_object_id                                = URL parameter, which provides object ID for the editing mode.
block_defaults_parameter_show_next_and_previous_info                          = Provides ability to display next and previous %type_names% filtered by the selected criteria.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_with_description                           = If enabled, only %type_names% with non-empty description will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_with_screenshot                            = If enabled, only %type_names% with screenshot #%1% uploaded will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_without_screenshot                         = If enabled, only %type_names% with empty screenshot #%1% will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_with_child_xxx                             = If enabled, only %type_names% with at least this number of child %relationship_type_names% will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_with_usage_xxx                             = If enabled, only %type_names% that are used in at least this number of connected %relationship_type_names% will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_only_with_content                               = If enabled, only %type_names% that are used in at least this number of connected content objects of various types (videos and/or albums and/or posts) are displayed in result.
block_defaults_parameter_skip_default_filter                                  = If enabled, this block will not do any default filering. Can be used to display inactive %type_names% where needed.
block_defaults_parameter_skip_xxx                                             = If specified, %type_names% with with this %1% will not be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_show_xxx                                             = If specified, only %type_names% with this %1% will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_skip_ids                                             = If specified, %type_names% with these IDs will not be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs).
block_defaults_parameter_show_ids                                             = If specified, only %type_names% with these IDs will be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs).
block_defaults_parameter_skip_property_xxx                                    = If specified, %type_names% with these %relationship_type_names% will not be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs, or titles).
block_defaults_parameter_show_property_xxx                                    = If specified, only %type_names% with these %relationship_type_names% will be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs, or titles).
block_defaults_parameter_skip_group_xxx                                       = If specified, %type_names% from these %relationship_type_names% will not be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs, or titles).
block_defaults_parameter_show_group_xxx                                       = If specified, only %type_names% from these %relationship_type_names% will be displayed (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs, or titles).
block_defaults_parameter_var_search                                           = URL parameter, which provides search text. If specified, only %type_names% that match the specified text will be displayed.
block_defaults_parameter_search_method                                        = Specifies search mode.
block_defaults_parameter_search_scope                                         = Configures whether both title and description should be searched.
block_defaults_parameter_search_redirect_enabled                              = Activates redirect to %type_name%'s page if result contains only one %type_name%. This can be used to immediately redirect users to the found %type_name%'s page instead of showing them list with the only element.
block_defaults_parameter_search_redirect_pattern                              = Used together with [kt|b]search_redirect_enabled[/kt|b] parameter. Provides URL pattern for creating redirection URL. The pattern should contain at least one of these tokens: [kt|b]%ID%[/kt|b] and / or [kt|b]%DIR%[/kt|b] that will be replaced with %type_name% ID / directory. Global %type_name% pattern setting (configured in [kt|b]Settings -> Website settings[/kt|b]) will be used by default if this parameter is empty.
block_defaults_parameter_search_empty_404                                     = Configures block to show 404 error on empty search results as if the page doesn't exist.
block_defaults_parameter_search_empty_redirect_to                             = Configures block to redirect to the given URL on empty search results. You can use [kt|b]%QUERY%[/kt|b] token here that will be replaced with search text.
block_defaults_parameter_search_blocked_404                                   = Configures block to show 404 error on search queries that contain blocked words as if the page doesn't exist. The list of blocked words is defined globally in [kt|b]Settings -> Website settings[/kt|b] area of admin panel.
block_defaults_parameter_search_blocked_redirect_to                           = Configures block to redirect to the given URL on search queries that contain blocked words. You can use [kt|b]%QUERY%[/kt|b] token here that will be replaced with search text. The list of blocked words is defined globally in [kt|b]Settings -> Website settings[/kt|b] area of admin panel.
block_defaults_parameter_search_caching_words                                 = Specifies the maximum number of search query words (separated by space or hyphen) when block should be actively caching results. It makes no much sense to cache multi-words queries, as chance they will be repeated within the same caching time is low, and thus caching won't make any benefit. By default the block will cache all single-word queries. Specify [kt|b]2[/kt|b] if you want KVS to cache all 2-worded queries as well.
block_defaults_parameter_enable_search_on_xxx                                 = Activates text search in %type_name% %relationship_type_names% and their synonyms.
block_defaults_parameter_show_xxx_info                                        = Enables %relationship_type_name% selection for every %type_name% in the list.
block_defaults_parameter_show_xxxs_info                                       = Enables %relationship_type_names% selection for every %type_name% in the list.
block_defaults_parameter_mode_related                                         = Enables this block to display related %type_names% for the other given base %type_name%, provided in URL. The value of this parameter selects related %type_names% calculation method by different criteria. In order this mode to work correctly you should activate one of the [kt|b]var_%type_single%_xxx[/kt|b] parameters below and provide its actual display value in URL to indicate base %type_name%.
block_defaults_parameter_mode_related_xxx_id                                  = Used together with [kt|b]mode_related[/kt|b] by %type_names% only. Specify %relationship_type_name% ID or external ID to restrict related calculation by %type_names% from this %relationship_type_name%.
block_defaults_parameter_var_mode_related                                     = URL parameter, which provides ability to dynamically switch related %type_names% calculation method. Overrides [kt|b]mode_related[/kt|b] parameter. The following values can be passed in URL: %1%.
block_defaults_parameter_mode_interconnected                                  = Enables this block to display interconnected %type_names% for the other base categorization object (not %type_name%), provided in URL. The value of this parameter selects connected %type_names% calculation method by different criteria. In order this mode to work correctly you should activate one of the [kt|b]var_xxx[/kt|b] parameters below and provide its actual display value in URL to indicate base categorization object.
block_defaults_parameter_var_skip_ids                                         = URL parameter name that will be used to dynamically exclude %type_names% with the given IDs (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs).
block_defaults_parameter_var_show_ids                                         = URL parameter name that will be used to dynamically display only %type_names% with the given IDs (comma separated list of numeric or external IDs).
block_defaults_parameter_var_title_section                                    = URL parameter, which provides ability to filter %type_names% by title's first N characters, for example by alphabet letters (A-Z). Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]section[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?section=A[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% starting with [kt|b]'A'[/kt|b] letter.
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dir_list                                     = URL parameter, which provides ability to filter %type_names% by %relationship_type_name% directory. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]%relationship_type_single%[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_single%=%relationship_type_single%_directory[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have %relationship_type_name% [kt|b]'%relationship_type_single%_directory'[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dirs_list                                    = URL parameter, which provides ability to filter %type_names% by multiple %relationship_type_name% directories. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]%relationship_type_multiple%[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_multiple%=%relationship_type_single%_directory_1,%relationship_type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have %relationship_type_names% [kt|b]'%relationship_type_single%_directory_1'[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]'%relationship_type_single%_directory_2'[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to filter items that have several specific %relationship_type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_multiple%=%relationship_type_single%_directory_1|%relationship_type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have both %relationship_type_names% [kt|b]'%relationship_type_single%_directory_1'[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]'%relationship_type_single%_directory_2'[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_id_list                                      = URL parameter, which provides ability to filter %type_names% by %relationship_type_name% ID. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]%relationship_type_single%_id[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_single%_id=123[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have %relationship_type_name% [kt|b]123[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_ids_list                                     = URL parameter, which provides ability to filter %type_names% by multiple %relationship_type_name% IDs. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]%relationship_type_single%_ids[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_single%_ids=123,124[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have %relationship_type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to filter items that have several specific %relationship_type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?%relationship_type_single%_ids=123|124[/kt|b] to show all %type_names% that have both %relationship_type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_skip_xxx_ids_list                                = URL parameter, which provides ability to exclude %type_names% by multiple %relationship_type_name% IDs. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]skip_%relationship_type_single%_ids[/kt|b]) and provide the actual filtering values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?skip_%relationship_type_single%_ids=123,124[/kt|b] to exclude all %type_names% that have %relationship_type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dir_view                                     = URL parameter, which provides ability to display %type_name% by its directory. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]dir[/kt|b]) and provide the actual display value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dir=%type_single%_directory[/kt|b] to show %type_name% [kt|b]'%type_single%_directory'[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_id_view                                      = URL parameter, which provides ability to display %type_name% by its numeric ID. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]id[/kt|b]) and provide the actual display value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?id=123[/kt|b] to show %type_name% [kt|b]123[/kt|b]. If enabled and the corresponding URL parameter contains numeric value, will have more priority than %type_name% directory.
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dir_related                                  = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_name% by its directory. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]dir[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dir=%type_single%_directory[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for %type_name% [kt|b]'%type_single%_directory'[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dirs_related                                 = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_names% by multiple %type_name% directories. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]dirs[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dirs=%type_single%_directory_1,%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for %type_names% [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_1[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to show related %type_names% for several base %type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dirs=%type_single%_directory_1|%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for both %type_names% [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_1[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_id_related                                   = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_name% by its numeric ID. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]id[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?id=123[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for %type_name% [kt|b]123[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_ids_related                                  = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_names% by multiple %type_name% IDs. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]ids[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?ids=123,124[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for %type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to show related %type_names% for several base %type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?ids=123|124[/kt|b] to show related %type_names% for both %type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dir_interconnected                           = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_name% by its directory. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]dir[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dir=%type_single%_directory[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for %type_name% [kt|b]'%type_single%_directory'[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_dirs_interconnected                          = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_names% by multiple %type_name% directories. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]dirs[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dirs=%type_single%_directory_1,%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for %type_names% [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_1[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for several base %type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?dirs=%type_single%_directory_1|%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for both %type_names% [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_1[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]%type_single%_directory_2[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_id_interconnected                            = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_name% by its numeric ID. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]id[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base value in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?id=123[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for %type_name% [kt|b]123[/kt|b].
block_defaults_parameter_var_xxx_ids_interconnected                           = URL parameter, which provides ability to specify base %type_names% by multiple %type_name% IDs. Activate this parameter (for instance [kt|b]ids[/kt|b]) and provide the actual base values in URL, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?ids=123,124[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for %type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]OR[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b]. It is possible to use vertical pipe separator [kt|b]|[/kt|b] for the 'AND' logic to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for several base %type_names% at the same time, e.g. [kt|b]https://URL?ids=123|124[/kt|b] to show interconnected %interconnected_type_names% for both %type_names% [kt|b]123[/kt|b] [kt|b]AND[/kt|b] [kt|b]124[/kt|b].
